    <stitle>No Idle APU/HVAC System - Troubleshooting - Generator</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Generator</title>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">No / low voltage output (16 to 24VAC)</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist style="alphalc">
            <item>
                <para>Low engine RPM - Increase engine speed to 3750 RPM (no load).</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Circuit breaker is tripped / failed - Reset / replace breaker.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Defective receptacle - Replace with 20A GFCI.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Failed stator - Test / replace.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Failed rotor - Test / replace.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Failed diode(s) - Test / replace rotor.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">No / minimum power output (8 to 12VAC)</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist style="alphalc">
            <item>
                <para>No load (correct RPM), failed diode or exciter winding - Test and replace.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Slightly low engine RPM - Increase engine speed to 3750 RPM (no load).</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Rotor wire off at diode solder joint - Test / replace rotor.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Rotor slipping from engine - Replace rotor &#38; PTO shaft.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Partially shorted rotor - Replace rotor.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">High voltage output</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist style="alphalc">
            <item>
                <para>High engine RPM - Reduce engine speed to 3750 RPM (no load).</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Voltage output drops</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist style="alphalc">
            <item>
                <para>Diode failure (diodes will test fine but they have a partial loss) - Replace rotor.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Low engine HP - see Engine Service Manual S12020.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Electrical load has a power factor below 0.7 - Remove inappropriate electrical load.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
